cs.DL, cs.IR, cs.SI, cs.CY, cs.CR 

The paper discusses statistical distributions for citation data, which is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science. cs.DL (Digital Libraries) is the most likely category as it deals with the management and analysis of digital information, including citation data. cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is also relevant as it deals with the retrieval and analysis of information, including citation data. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) may also be relevant as citation networks are a type of social network. cs.CY (Computational Geometry) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) are less likely but still possible as they may involve analysis of citation data in their respective fields.
